elements.value: Let's take a look at the state of the market and where Kentico is headed ⎯ its vision, mission, strategy, and brand ⎯ as well as updates to our roadmaps for Kentico EMS and Kentico Kontent.
Connecting the Dots in Your Digital Experience Stack

Whether you need to send your content for automatic translation, fill in missing product data, or integrate with other systems in your stack, there are APIs and webhooks available for you. See how to use them to get the full potential out of headless CMS.
Using Kentico 12 MVC with Azure DevOps

How can you provide an up-to-date view of your project to product owners and key stakeholders without giving them some form of access to your development environments? Microsoft Azure DevOps development teams can provide near real-time updates to those who need them without them needing to perform the updates themselves. In this talk we’ll consider building the solution code for both the public MVC site and the Portal-based admin site, running continuous integration tasks, and deploying all of that to Microsoft Azure Web Services.

Have you implemented Kentico at scale? Is your focus the customer experience? Without the right foundations, you could be falling short of your full potential. Join this talk to learn what is really possible with real-world case studies of Kentico at scale. As your central Martech platform, see Kentico in action for high-traffic and high-revenue sites, evaluate your company’s Kentico maturity, and learn how to ready yourself for growth with a focus on innovation.
From the Ground Up: Kentico 12 MVC Design Patterns

Since November 2018, two worlds have been colliding to great effect — ASP.NET MVC and Kentico CMS. Now, Kentico developers have even more ability to customize the way that content, stored and organized in Kentico CMS, is delivered to website visitors. With this new room for customization comes an opportunity to implement powerful, elegant, and forward thinking patterns, and best practices. In this talk I will present some important design patterns and practices you can implement in your Kentico 12 MVC applications, starting with modern .NET tools, code organization, designing for automated testability, and leveraging the power of MVC and Web API.
Welcome to the World of Integrations

Where does Kentico fit in the modern world of integrations? What solutions can be combined to create that ultimate digital experience? If you're looking to integrate Kentico Kontent with other SaaS products on the market quickly, then join this talk with case studies and demo.

Where is the Kentico platform headed and what can you expect to see in our next major release? What are the plans for future compatibility with .NET Standard and why is it crucial for digital businesses to use technologies compatible with .NET Core?
The True Power of Headless CMS Is in Its Marriage With IoT

The true power and ROI potential of using a headless CMS are unleashed when its collaborative content management capabilities are combined with an IoT system – bringing the omnichannel scenario into practice. In our practical showcase, we will introduce how content stored in Kentico Kontent can easily be made location-aware and can help boost engagement and spending on the customer side, while providing analytics data on the client side. See the power that the combination of UWB technology (hotly rumored to be part of the next iPhone release) and Kentico Kontent brings.
Kentico + Azure DevOps: Streamlining Your Kentico Development and Deployment Process
Learn how to adopt DevOps practices and implementing CI/CD processes to streamline development and deployment of your Kentico projects using Kentico CI, Azure DevOps, Azure App Services, Azure SQL.

Why Hold a Tech Conference?
